==English==
===Etymology===
From the latin [[sibilare]], to [[hiss]].
===Adjective===
[[Category:English adjectives]]
'''sibilant'''
# Characterized by a [[hissing]] sound such as the 's' or 'sh' in 'sash' or 'surge'.

===Quotations===
*'''1960''': Harper Lee, ''To Kill A Mockingbird''
*:She had a curious habit of prefacing everyting she said with a soft sibilant sound.<br/>"S-s-s Grace," she said, "it's just like I was telling Brother Hutson the other day. 'S-s-s Brother Hutson,' I said, 'looks like we're fighting a losing battle, a losing battle.' I said."

===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
'''sibilant'''
# A [[hissing]] sound such as the 's' or 'sh' in 'sash' or 'surge'.

